<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Economy: Machine and electronic manufacturing, automobile and aviation industry, coffee, soil, sugar cane, tourism, oil&amp;sub-products (gasoline, diesel, etc), textiles, energy production (not sufficient, however, to attend its demand); it is the business-economic center of Brazil, most bigger Brazilians companies and foreign companies installed in Brazil have their headquarters installed in this region</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Transport: The region is heavily covered by highways, and to some extent, railways. Railways and rivers are used mainly for freight, and used when they are present. Regional, domestic and international air routes connects larger cities, with the main hubs for <link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../942/1942.xml">
airlines</link> in the country</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

