</it>
</indent>

<list>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Area: 577.214 km² (6,2%)</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Population: 25.800.000 hab (43,46 hab/km², 12,5%)</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

GDP: ~91,5bi US$ (16,5%)</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

HDI: ~0.831</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Climate: Subtropical in almost all the entire region, hot to moderately hot in the summer and mild (though cold for Brazilian standards) and very humid winters. Snow is extremely rare except for the highlands where some occasional light snow might fall. The northeast part of the region has a Tropical climate, being hot in the summer and warm/cool during the winter, with some cold days.</entry>
