<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Transport: Highways and railways are heavily present throughout the region, although the latter is mainly used for freight. Rivers are used when possible.</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Vegetation: Rainforests along the coast (Mata Atlântica), tropical semiciduous in the north and west (Araucárias) and prairie-like vegetation in the south (<link xlink:type="simple" xlink:href="../252/373252.xml">
Pampas</link>). Little native vegetation still actually remains</entry>
<entry level="1" type="bullet">

Marcant characteristics: The South region is characterized by its high standard of living, with the best social indicators of the country - The best city to live in and the best capitals to live in are all here:<link>
